attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB executable, ARM aarch64, version 1 (SYSV), dynamically linked, interpreter /lib/ld-linux-aarch64.so.1, BuildID[sha1]=7776106c2c24f21e2245788042bb5f4afd30fd17, for GNU/Linux 5.4.0, with debug_info, not stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factors were that it has known exploits and it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a ransomware variant targeting aarch64 Linux systems, attributed to the '8Base' group. It recursively traverses the filesystem, encrypts files using a ChaCha20/Curve25519 hybrid encryption scheme, and renames them. After encrypting a directory, it drops a ransom note containing a Tor .onion URL. Key malicious behaviors include file encryption (`file_process`, `buffer_crypt`), recursive file searching (`files_find_recursive`), file renaming (`file_rename`), and dropping a ransom note (`file_write_message`). The ability to run as a background process (`daemon`) is also present.
